<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,1681,1887]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
REMARKS.—This is a very small species (body length 12.20–13.50) with piceous markings of the head, thorax, postclypeus, and ventral abdomen. This is the only known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[881,972,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Herrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[881,972,1718,1743]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Herrera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where the male operculum is piceous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,1681,1887]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
